---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 28, 2026";
---

<Layout
    title="Privacy Policy — Wardrobe"
    description="What Wardrobe collects, why, and how to opt out. Short and honest."
    chrome="neutral"
>
    <main class="wrap">
        <article class="prose">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="meta"><strong>Last updated:</strong> {lastUpdated}</p>

            <p>Wardrobe is a side project by Martin Ibsen.</p>

            <h2>What we collect</h2>

            <p>
                <strong>Email addresses</strong>, when you voluntarily sign up
                via our forms. Stored in Loops
                (<a href="https://loops.so" target="_blank" rel="noopener">loops.so</a>)
                and used to send theme drop notifications + occasional builder
                notes. We don't sell or share with third parties.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Anonymous analytics</strong> via PostHog. We track page
                views, theme preferences, and signup conversions to improve the
                site. No personal data, no cross-site tracking. Anonymized after
                30 days.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Cookies</strong> — only what's needed to remember your
                consent choice and PostHog session if you've opted in.
            </p>

            <h2>What we don't do</h2>

            <ul>
                <li>No ads</li>
                <li>No selling data</li>
                <li>No retargeting pixels</li>
                <li>No "we may share with partners"</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Your rights (GDPR)</h2>

            <p>
                You can request deletion of your data anytime by replying to any
                email or emailing
                <a href="mailto:martin@martinibsen.dk">martin@martinibsen.dk</a>.
            </p>

            <p>
                To unsubscribe from emails: click the unsubscribe link in any
                email, or visit your preferences via the Loops link.
            </p>

            <h2>Contact</h2>

            <p>
                <a href="mailto:martin@martinibsen.dk">martin@martinibsen.dk</a>
            </p>

            <p class="footnote">
                Built with Wardrobe —
                <a href="https://wardrobeui.com">wardrobeui.com</a>
            </p>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .wrap {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 64px 24px 96px;
    }
    .prose {
        color: #0a0a0a;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .prose h1 {
        font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 48px);
        line-height: 1.1;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 0 16px;
    }
    .prose h2 {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 40px 0 12px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .prose p {
        font-size: 17px;
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        color: #262626;
    }
    .prose .meta {
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #525252;
        margin: 0 0 32px;
    }
    .prose ul {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        padding-left: 22px;
        font-size: 17px;
        color: #262626;
    }
    .prose ul li { margin: 4px 0; }
    .prose a {
        color: #0a0a0a;
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .prose a:hover { color: #525252; }
    .prose .footnote {
        margin-top: 56px;
        padding-top: 24px;
        border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #525252;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .wrap { padding: 32px 20px 64px; }
        .prose p, .prose ul { font-size: 16px; }
    }
</style>
